<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-159-052 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 707 399</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 6 1991 n419 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM marketing program gets mixed reviews.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grace, Tim; Hedlund, Kristen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Value-added resellers (VARs) and dealers greet IBM's newmultimedia channel marketing program with mixed reactions.andO;Resellers say that though they felt the vendor's proactive rolewould be good for developing the market they are doubtful aboutthe income to be made in the multimedia market in the near term.andO;The new marketing program is being offered to the vendor's PCIndustry Remarketers (VARs) and authorized resellers.andP;  Remarketersand dealers, in order to receive special designation as a programparticipant, must meet a number of criteria, such as sending amarketing and a technical employee to training, developing amultimedia marketing plan, taking part in the IBM TechnicalAdvisor and Commitment to Customer Satisfaction programs andconducting quarterly multimedia seminars.andP;  The vendor'sdirect-sales force will turn over leads to dealers and will becompensated and receive a bonus for VAR or dealer sales.andP;  Thevendor plans to sign between 100 and 150 resellers to the program.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Marketing).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyValue-Added ResellersComputer RetailingDealers and AgentsMultimedia Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>